rows.label: qst202503_msg0001
rows.name:
92% of enemy forces neutralized.
Remaining enemy forces incapable
of proceeding with combat.

rows.label: qst202503_msg0003
rows.name:
A search of the area reveals no sign
of new units emerging.

rows.label: qst202503_msg0004
rows.name:
I...incredible...
We really take out all those enemies...

rows.label: qst202503_msg0005
rows.name:
You say "we"... Mostly it was down to
that crazy power of KOS-MOS Re:'s.

rows.label: qst202503_msg0006
rows.name:
It really was crazy powerful.
I've never seen anything like it.

rows.label: qst202503_msg0007
rows.name:
I merely selected the optimal course
of action after analyzing all alternatives.

rows.label: qst202503_msg0010
rows.name:
Yeah, if it weren't for you we'd
never have beaten that lot!

rows.label: qst202503_msg0012
rows.name:
That attack you used, though...
I wouldn't be surprised if it was
detected in neighboring countries.

rows.label: qst202503_msg0013
rows.name:
Yeah, I reckon that light will have
been visible from Luxuria and
Superbia at least.

rows.label: qst202503_msg0014
rows.name:
Um, so have we accidentally caused
a bit of an international commotion?

rows.label: qst202503_msg0015
rows.name:
The national leaders may need to
be warned about these artificial
Blades, as well.

rows.label: qst202503_msg0016
rows.name:
Perhaps our next course of
action should be to report in to
King Serich.

rows.label: qst202503_msg0017
rows.name:
Yeah, we'd better explain ourselves
and clear up any misunderstandings.

rows.label: qst202503_msg0018
rows.name:
My old man can get pretty antsy.
Let's head to Theoscaldia Palace
and set his mind at ease.
